  <summary date="2015-03-23T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Family Health Care Flexibility Act

This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to repeal provisions added by the&#160;Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act that: (1) restrict payments from health savings accounts, Archer medical savings accounts, and health flexible spending and reimbursement arrangements for medications to prescription drugs and insulin only (thus allowing payments for over-the-counter medications); and (2) impose a $2,500 limitation on salary reduction contributions to a health flexible spending arrangement under a cafeteria plan.</summary>
